00:14:54,833 --> 00:14:56,400
And what would your name be?

260
00:14:56,466 --> 00:14:57,733
Nice to meet you.

261
00:14:57,800 --> 00:15:00,166
And what would your name be...?

262
00:15:08,233 --> 00:15:09,166
But even then,

263
00:15:09,233 --> 00:15:12,466
I still couldn't send
her out to be repaired.

264
00:15:12,533 --> 00:15:14,200
Even if it was
only a little bit,

265
00:15:14,266 --> 00:15:15,666
or even just once in a while...

266
00:15:15,733 --> 00:15:18,133
The fact that she
could still remember me

267
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:20,166
with that broken hard
drive was something

268
00:15:20,233 --> 00:15:23,200
I just couldn't bring
myself to let go of.

269
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:27,200
But then, one rainy day

270
00:15:27,266 --> 00:15:29,433
after she'd been
like that for a while,

271
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:31,933
we went out shopping together.

272
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:35,666
By that time, it was
very hard for her

273
00:15:35,733 --> 00:15:37,866
to live even a
simple everyday life.

274
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:40,233
I never knew what she might do

275
00:15:40,300 --> 00:15:41,833
if I took my eyes off of her.

276
00:15:44,466 --> 00:15:45,800
I thought about her constantly,

277
00:15:45,866 --> 00:15:49,133
and I couldn't sleep,
there was nothing I could do.

278
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:51,700
I guess I was in a daze.

279
00:16:45,566 --> 00:16:47,866
Nice to meet you.

280
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:58,166
Nice to meet you.

281
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,200
I'm sure she was in such a state

282
00:17:07,266 --> 00:17:09,100
that she didn't understand
the consequences

283
00:17:09,166 --> 00:17:11,433
of being hit by a truck.

284
00:17:11,500 --> 00:17:14,833
But, I somehow felt
that she'd sacrificed

285
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:17,433
her own life to save me.

286
00:17:26,066 --> 00:17:27,833
Pretty strange, huh?

287
00:17:27,900 --> 00:17:29,500
She was still able to
do an incredible thing

288
00:17:29,566 --> 00:17:31,833
like that when she
could barely even function.

289
00:17:31,900 --> 00:17:33,333
No, it's not strange!

290
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:35,133
Not in the least.

291
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:36,333
I think she saved
your life even though

292
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:38,500
she knew what would happen.

293
00:17:40,766 --> 00:17:42,400
Thanks for saying that.

294
00:17:45,433 --> 00:17:46,533
Immediately after the accident,

295
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:49,400
I took her to the shop
where I bought her.

296
00:17:49,466 --> 00:17:51,566
But they said that
she was so torn up

297
00:17:51,633 --> 00:17:53,466
that they could
never re-boot her.

298
00:17:54,433 --> 00:17:56,266
Her body was shattered.

299
00:17:56,333 --> 00:17:57,500
They said if I wanted,

300
00:17:57,566 --> 00:18:00,400
they'd try to find another
one of the same model.

301
00:18:00,466 --> 00:18:02,133
A different one
that looked the same.

302
00:18:04,533 --> 00:18:07,800
But, to me, there could
never be another "her."

303
00:18:07,866 --> 00:18:11,500
She was a Persocom,
and not a living creature,

304
00:18:12,666 --> 00:18:15,400
but for me, she had
died there in the rain.

305
00:18:20,266 --> 00:18:22,033
I knew that there
was nothing to repair;

306
00:18:22,100 --> 00:18:24,700
she couldn't feel or
remember anything anymore.

307
00:18:24,766 --> 00:18:26,533
But...

308
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:28,733
I still remember her.

309
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:30,866
I remember everything about her.

310
00:18:30,933 --> 00:18:35,233
Her face, her voice,
her movements...

311
00:18:35,300 --> 00:18:38,766
The good times
and the bad times.

312
00:18:40,233 --> 00:18:42,566
I'm pretty sure I'll
never forget any of that.

313
00:18:43,900 --> 00:18:46,233
That's just how
you feel, isn't it?

314
00:18:46,533 --> 00:18:48,866
Even if Chi doesn't remember
what the two of you have shared,

315
00:18:48,933 --> 00:18:51,366
you'll always remember,
won't you, Motosuwa?

316
00:18:53,933 --> 00:18:55,633
If something happened to Chi,

317
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:57,966
you'd still remember
her, wouldn't you?

318
00:18:58,500 --> 00:18:59,766
Yes.

319
00:18:59,833 --> 00:19:02,166
So it wouldn't have been
all for nothing, then.

320
00:19:02,233 --> 00:19:04,200
Even if they were
able to erase it

321
00:19:04,266 --> 00:19:06,000
from the hard drive somehow,

322
00:19:06,066 --> 00:19:08,600
not as long as you
still remember, Motosuwa.

323
00:19:08,666 --> 00:19:12,200
That's why you need to find Chi.

324
00:19:12,533 --> 00:19:13,566
Yes.

325
00:19:13,633 --> 00:19:15,333
Even though I don't have
an idea where she could be,

326
00:19:15,400 --> 00:19:17,033
I'm gonna look for her.

327
00:19:17,100 --> 00:19:19,266
I'm sure she'll
be waiting for you.

328
00:19:20,700 --> 00:19:21,800
Yeah.

329
00:19:30,100 --> 00:19:31,100
Motosuwa!

330
00:19:31,166 --> 00:19:32,700
That might be who took Chi!

331
00:19:35,266 --> 00:19:36,566
What's going on?

332
00:19:38,233 --> 00:19:39,500
Chi.

333
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:44,000
Hey you!

334
00:19:50,633 --> 00:19:51,600
Yumi?

335
00:19:58,733 --> 00:19:59,800
Miss Ohmura.

336
00:19:59,866 --> 00:20:01,166
Huh?

337
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:04,000
Yumi!

338
00:20:04,066 --> 00:20:05,266
You might as well
save your breath.

339
00:20:05,333 --> 00:20:06,466
Huh?

340
00:20:06,533 --> 00:20:08,866
I'm afraid she's not gonna
come back as long as I'm here.

341
00:20:09,466 --> 00:20:10,366
Well, as you can see,

342
00:20:10,433 --> 00:20:12,466
she gets really sad
whenever I'm around her.

343
00:20:12,533 --> 00:20:15,000
Do you know
something about Yumi?

344
00:20:19,433 --> 00:20:20,700
For the moment,
the most important thing

345
00:20:20,766 --> 00:20:22,766
for us to do is to find Chi.

346
00:20:24,133 --> 00:20:25,266
What's this file?

347
00:20:25,333 --> 00:20:27,500
It's an access log from
the custom-made Persocom

348
00:20:27,566 --> 00:20:29,300
website where
I posted that message

349
00:20:29,366 --> 00:20:30,633
about Chi a while back.

350
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:32,433
I had it sent to me.

351
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:35,033
I'm surprised that the
webmaster would do this.

352
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:37,666
They owe me, so I cashed
in the favor this time.

353
00:20:38,033 --> 00:20:40,066
With a list, I can check
them off one by one

354
00:20:40,133 --> 00:20:41,500
and see if any of
them match the person

355
00:20:41,566 --> 00:20:42,733
who sent that image.

356
00:20:44,033 --> 00:20:46,633
The reason Miss Chi
disappeared like this might be

357
00:20:46,700 --> 00:20:51,033
because I didn't think through
before I posted on that site.

358
00:20:51,100 --> 00:20:53,400
Sorry to cause you such trouble.

359
00:20:54,433 --> 00:20:57,866
It's all because I had
to open my big mouth.

360
00:21:01,566 --> 00:21:02,500
Thank you.

361
00:21:02,566 --> 00:21:03,466
What?

362
00:21:03,533 --> 00:21:04,466
If you hadn't brought it up,

363
00:21:04,533 --> 00:21:06,666
it never would have even
occurred to me, Yuzuki.

364
00:21:06,733 --> 00:21:08,366
It was a very good suggestion.

365
00:21:09,566 --> 00:21:11,166
Lord Minoru.

366
00:21:11,233 --> 00:21:13,666
I'm very happy that
you brought it up.

367
00:21:13,733 --> 00:21:15,700
Thank you, Lord Minoru.

368
00:21:15,766 --> 00:21:18,166
I just thought that your sister
would have done the same thing,

369
00:21:18,233 --> 00:21:20,233
so that's why
I mentioned it to you.

370
00:21:20,300 --> 00:21:21,966
Well you're right.

371
00:21:22,033 --> 00:21:24,466
My sister truly was very kind,

372
00:21:24,533 --> 00:21:26,900
and would gently point out
my mistakes and oversights.

373
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:30,933
Oh, I see.

374
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:32,533
But, I wasn't happy just

375
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:36,166
because you did something that
my sister would have done.

376
00:21:43,533 --> 00:21:45,933
New mail has arrived. This is...

377
00:21:46,700 --> 00:21:47,833
What's wrong?

378
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:49,400
The return address matches

379
00:21:49,466 --> 00:21:52,133
the one that sent
the image of Miss Chi!

380
00:21:57,233 --> 00:22:01,300
Yumi and Mr. Ueda, they
know each other somehow,

381
00:22:01,366 --> 00:22:05,166
but for some reason,
Yumi never even mentioned it.

382
00:22:11,466 --> 00:22:13,233
I can't think about that now,

383
00:22:13,300 --> 00:22:14,566
I have to look for Chi!

384
00:22:14,633 --> 00:22:15,700
Let's go, Sumomo!

385
00:22:15,766 --> 00:22:16,833
Aye!

386
00:23:57,300 --> 00:24:02,000
I begin my search again today
for the one who is only for me.

387
00:24:02,333 --> 00:24:06,566
The person who will love me
because I am who I am.

388
00:24:06,633 --> 00:24:09,133
The person who
will still love me

389
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:12,100
even if I cannot
grant his dreams.

390
00:24:12,166 --> 00:24:16,433
The special one for Chi.

391
00:24:16,500 --> 00:24:20,866
Next episode, Chobits:
"Chi Wants."

392
00:24:20,933 --> 00:24:25,366
The one for Chi
and only for Chi.

